  "summary": "Main\nBy Jeffrey Landsberg\nChina's total electricity generation came in at 768.5 billion kilowatt hours last month. This has marked a month-on-month increase of 50.6 billion kilowatt hours (7%) and is up year-on-year by 28.6 billion kilowatt hours (4%). Coal-derived electricity generation totaled 487 billion kilowatt hours.",
